<subSubSection id="C5BCF8D2320AFFF25CCF00C9FB91FEEB" pageId="4" pageNumber="405" type="description">
<paragraph id="8D19AB59320AFFF25CCF00C9FC7DFF08" blockId="4.[166,1224,175,298]" box="[219,905,175,202]" pageId="4" pageNumber="405">
D i s t r i b u t i o n. 
<collectingCountry id="F5B1EBC9320AFFF25DA400D6FDEBFF0B" box="[432,543,175,201]" name="Kyrgyzstan" pageId="4" pageNumber="405">Kirghizia</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry id="F5B1EBC9320AFFF25E3E00C9FDA8FF08" box="[554,604,176,202]" name="Iran" pageId="4" pageNumber="405">Iran</collectingCountry>
(Khaganinia et al., 2010).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8D19AB59320AFFF25CCF00A9FB91FEEB" blockId="4.[166,1224,175,298]" pageId="4" pageNumber="405">
D i a g n o s t i c c h a r a c t e r s. Eye bare, antenna black, third antennal segment large and covered by brownish microtrichia, antennal socket separated (
<figureCitation id="159DB7DC320AFFF25FAD0096FC01FECB" box="[953,1013,239,265]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="3.[170,203,1674,1696]" captionTargetBox="[176,1228,642,1642]" captionTargetId="figure-285@3.[170,1229,636,1646]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="Fig. 1. Cheilosia aerea (a–c): a — dorsal view of female, b — lateral view of head of female, c — male genitalia; C. cumanica (d–f): d — dorsal view of female, e — frontal view of head of female, f — male genitalia; C. lola, female (g–h): g — dorsal view, h — frontal view of head. Рис. 1. Cheilosia aerea (a–c): a — самка, вид сверху; b — голова самки, латеральный вид, c — гениталии самца; C. cumanica (d–f): d — самка, вид сверху, e — голова самки, фронтальный вид, f — гениталии самца; C. lola, самка (g–h): g — вид сверху, h — голова, фронтальный вид." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6449151" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6449151/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="405">fig. 1</figureCitation>
, 
<emphasis id="BFD2774B320AFFF258170096FBE6FECB" box="[1027,1042,239,265]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="405">h</emphasis>
), sides of facial knob bare; wing hyaline (
<figureCitation id="159DB7DC320AFFF25DDB0176FDFEFEEB" box="[463,522,271,297]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="3.[170,203,1674,1696]" captionTargetBox="[176,1228,642,1642]" captionTargetId="figure-285@3.[170,1229,636,1646]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="Fig. 1. Cheilosia aerea (a–c): a — dorsal view of female, b — lateral view of head of female, c — male genitalia; C. cumanica (d–f): d — dorsal view of female, e — frontal view of head of female, f — male genitalia; C. lola, female (g–h): g — dorsal view, h — frontal view of head. Рис. 1. Cheilosia aerea (a–c): a — самка, вид сверху; b — голова самки, латеральный вид, c — гениталии самца; C. cumanica (d–f): d — самка, вид сверху, e — голова самки, фронтальный вид, f — гениталии самца; C. lola, самка (g–h): g — вид сверху, h — голова, фронтальный вид." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6449151" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6449151/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="405">fig. 1</figureCitation>
, 
<emphasis id="BFD2774B320AFFF25E030169FDD7FEEB" box="[535,547,272,297]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="405">g</emphasis>
); legs mostly black, except tibia pale in two sides.
</paragraph>
